cs.THEORY, cs.DM, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.CG 

This paper deals with theoretical aspects of self-assembly systems and their simulation powers, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.THEORY sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the study of hierarchical systems, which could fall under the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. The use of tile-based models and glues along their edges suggests a possible connection to the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the exploration of simulation powers and limitations, which could also fall under the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category.
